I suggest adding two major cases to avoid going through the whole if-chain for everything that doesn't match at all. We can also drop the "Py_SIZE() for builtins" case, I think, because the set that it uses for the lookup does not currently contain any builtin types.
```suggestion
    def _find_special_capi_len_function(self, typ) -> Optional[str]:
        if typ.is_extension_type:
            if typ.entry.qualified_name in self._ext_types_with_pysize:
                return 'Py_SIZE'
        elif typ.is_builtin_type:
            if typ.is_pystr_type:
                …
            …
        return None

```
Oh, and please move the `_ext_types_with_pysize` set definition above the new method. It's too hidden where it is now.
